\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Unknown\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Φιλιστοῦς\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Φιλιστοῦς\">\u003Cspan data-text=\"Φιλιστοῦς\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"Φιλιστώ\">ΦΙΛΙΣΤΟΥΣ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Dmitry Dundua, Robert Crellin\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic-simple-lemmatized\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan data-text=\"Φιλιστοῦς\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"Φιλιστώ\">ΦΙΛΙΣΤΟΥΣ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic120_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"Scan from IGMusPal, courtesy Museo Archeologico Regionale Antonino Salinas\" src=\"ISic120_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001209.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"Scan from IGMusPal, courtesy Museo Archeologico Regionale Antonino Salinas\" src=\"ISic001209-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>  \u003Cspan>Text of IG\u003C/span>  \u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>(Tomb) of Philisto\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>The name \u003Ca href=\"http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?name=%CE%A6%CE%B9%CE%BB%CE%B9%CF%83%CF%84%CF%8E\" target=\"_blank\">Φιλιστώ\u003C/a> is not common; it is also attested in Sicily in the theatre seat inscriptions of \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001262\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001262\u003C/a> (Taormina). Although dated on the grounds of letter forms to the C2-1 BC by Manni Piraino, the evidence from the necropolis suggests the range C3-2 BC is more plausible.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Salinas NSA 1886 464 no.b \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Kaibel 1890 \u003Ca href=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\" target=\"_blank\">382d\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Hoffmann 1904 5208d \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000817\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000817\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Manni Piraino 1973 123 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000531\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000531\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Sofia 2015 107 and fig.110 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001575\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001575\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"handnote\"> \u003Cp>Regular plain letters. Phi is slightly taller than the rest, but with a small circular eye; sigma has horizontal top and bottom bars, with the diagonals joined by a curve; omicron is smaller than the other letters and mid-line.\u003C/p> Line 1  30-35  Interlineation line 1 to 2  NA  \u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Com